    <div class="section second">
      <div class="phead">ABOUT</div>
      <hr>
      <div><p> I am a senior at <a href="http://www.barnard.edu" class="link"> Barnard College of Columbia University in the City of New York </a>. Inspired by my internship experience at <a href="http://www.reeltheapp.com/" class="link">Reel</a>, a mobile communications app startup, I created my own major to combine my interests in both economics and computer science. On top of my coursework, I am also teaching myself to become a front-end web developer, which is both wonderful and occasionally frustrating. </p>


		<!--picture of me for about section-->
		<div class="mediv">
			<img src="contactpic.jpg" style="height: 200px; width: 270px">
		</div>
		

		<p>When not working or studying, I like to play with my dog, teach myself to play the ukulele, and read about global food systems. My two favorite books on this topic are <a href= "http://michaelpollan.com/books/in-defense-of-food/" class="link">In Defense of Food</a> and <a href ="http://www.thethirdplate.com/" class="link">The Third Plate</a>. I hope that one day I can help to address the immense problem of food deserts in urban areas. My time at <a href="http://thefoodproject.org/" class="link">The Food Project</a> gave me a firsthand look at the extensive health and cultural implications of not having access to fresh food.</p>


		<p style="inline">Between June and July of 2015, I spent a month pursuing my love of travel, adventuring and traveling around Europe by myself. I stayed in Dublin, London, and France in Paris and Brittany. When I wasn't looking at pretty old paintings or castles, I took a lot of <a href="https://instagram.com/p/5JiqKXIHJ1/?taken-by=jrgron" class="link"> cheesy pictures</a> and tried a lot of new foods, except snails.</p>
         <p style="inline">Interested in my professional details? You can check out and download my resume <a href="http://www.jgron.com/JuliaGronCV_2015.pdf" class="link">here.</a></p> 

